Class TravelTimeLocal

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.traveltime.TravelTimeLocal

  • public class TravelTimeLocal
extends java.lang.Object
    Manage travel-time calculations locally, but in a manner similar to the travel time server pool.

    Ray Buland

                       boolean readEllip,
                       boolean readTopo)
                throws java.io.IOException
        Initialize auxiliary data common to all models.
        Parameters:
        readStats - If true, read the phase statistics
        readEllip - If true, read the ellipticity corrections
        readTopo - If true, read the topography file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the auxiliary data reads fail

        public void travelTimeSession(java.lang.String earthModel,
                              double sourceDepth,
                              java.lang.String[] phases,
                              boolean returnAllPhases,
                              boolean returnBackBranches,
                              boolean tectonic,
                              boolean useRSTT)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Set up a "simple" travel-time session.
        Parameters:
        earthModel - Earth model name
        sourceDepth - Source depth in kilometers
        phases - Array of phase use commands
        returnAllPhases - If true, provide all phases
        returnBackBranches - If true, return all back branches
        tectonic - If true, map Pb and Sb onto Pg and Sg
        useRSTT - If true, use RSTT crustal phases
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If the depth is out of range
